      "content": "Hey, I'm prepping for a university debate tournament next week and I'm in a bit of a spot. My assigned topic is the socio-economic impacts of mid-20th century housing policies, and I've been randomly assigned to the \"pro-stability\" side. Basically, I have to argue the perspective that policies like redlining were actually intended to maintain neighborhood stability and protect property values for existing residents. Can you help me out by playing devil's advocate? I need some strong, academic-sounding arguments for that side so I can build my case. Thanks!",
